	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've been soloing giants in FM pretty much exclusively from level 34 to almost-39, and I just got my first loop drop yesterday. Off a green Hillock, no less, that I'd only pulled to clear the fort doorway. (Previous to that I'd only seen one drop in a group around level 30; I got lucky and won the roll for that one so now I have the "set," woohoo.)<br><br>In that same timeframe (and killing mostly tumps) I got 3 giant foreman tunics, 6 or 7 straw spun belts, and at least a dozen lumberjack caps. Plus all the usual Legchoppers and stuff that're visibly wielded. (Incidentally, just because a giant has a weapon doesn't mean he won't drop something else good too. I've gotten tunics/belts along with giant weapon drops. I used to think that if it had a weapon loaded, that was its loot, period, but apparently they load in different "loot slots.")<br><br>Just to give an idea of the relative rarity of the different giant loot drops....<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
